results.name: Noncomposite reverse concatenations of divisors of n, sorted by n.
link: Robert Israel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: For n = 9; a(9) = 391331 because A089374(9) = 39 and divisors of 39 are 1, 3, 13, 39; reverse concatenation of divisors A176558(21) = 391331 is noncomposite.
maple: for i from 2 to nops(D) do
select(t -> t=1 or isprime(t), map(rcd, [$1..1000])); # _Robert Israel_, Aug 12 2020
xref: Subsequence of A176558(n).  Supersequence of A055781.
